<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-29T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10483:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-29T13:00:00+03:00">April 29, 1941—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 30—9:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>364. My 363, April 29, noon.<note n="15" xml:id="d211fn15">Not
                                    printed.</note> Although the advance into Egypt is reported to
                                have halted a short distance over the frontier I understand that it
                                has already served to give the German and Italian forces control of
                                two important advance airfields and the passes down the escarpment
                                at Halfaya and Sollum.</p>
                            <p>In the course of my latest conversations with the highest military
                                authorities here the comment has been only general and to the effect
                                that critical times are ahead.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>